{
  "_comment": "EXAMPLE FILE — NOT ACTIVE. Copy to `.mcp.json` at repo root to enable. See README below for context.",
  "_readme": [
    "Team-shared MCP servers for Spacebot.",
    "",
    "HOW TO USE:",
    "  1. Copy this file to `.mcp.json` (drop the `.example` suffix) at the repo root.",
    "  2. Commit it so every teammate (and every agent instance) gets the same MCP surface on project load.",
    "  3. Ensure prerequisites are met (see each server's `_prerequisites` key).",
    "  4. Claude Code auto-loads `.mcp.json` when it's in the repo root.",
    "",
    "WHY TEAM-SHARED:",
    "  Per-user MCP setup drifts. A committed `.mcp.json` guarantees code review, PR automation,",
    "  and ad-hoc repo queries all resolve against the same tool surface. It also makes hosted",
    "  agent runs (GitHub Actions, remote triggers, CI scripts) reproducible.",
    "",
    "ALREADY-CONFIGURED GLOBAL SERVERS (NOT DUPLICATED HERE):",
    "  - code-review-graph   — project-scoped, global install",
    "  - serena              — project-scoped, global install",
    "  - claude-mem          — user-scoped, global install",
    "  - context7            — user-scoped, global install",
    "  - chrome-devtools     — user-scoped, global install",
    "  - playwright          — user-scoped, global install",
    "",
    "  Only servers that are missing or should be team-shared belong in THIS file.",
    "",
    "PROMOTED-TO-TEAM-SHARED:",
    "  - microsoft-docs      — added 2026-04-21 as part of the Entra ID rollout (Phase 3",
    "                          depends on Microsoft Graph docs; Phase 6 depends on MSAL.js",
    "                          docs). Previously user-scoped via the microsoft-docs plugin.",
    "                          Keep the plugin install too; this file just makes it",
    "                          resolvable inside agents that don't inherit user-scoped MCP."
  ],

  "mcpServers": {
    "github": {
      "_purpose": "Native GitHub operations: issues, PRs, Actions, Dependabot alerts (57 currently open on main).",
      "_why_team_shared": "Admin-merge patterns (PRs #78/#79), CI triage, and Dependabot sweeps all touch GitHub state. Teammate-consistent toolset matters.",
      "_prerequisites": "`gh auth login` OR a GITHUB_TOKEN env var with `repo`, `read:org`, `workflow` scopes.",
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-github"],
      "env": {
        "GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN": "${GITHUB_TOKEN}"
      }
    },

    "microsoft-docs": {
      "_purpose": "Authoritative Microsoft Learn + Azure SDK docs. Covers Microsoft Graph (Entra Phase 3's @odata.nextLink pagination per A-11, /me/photo/$value per A-19), MSAL.js v5 (Phase 6 cacheLocation gotchas per A-16/A-17, /api/me endpoint contract per A-18), Tauri OAuth redirect URI rules (Phase 8 IP-literal requirement), Conditional Access semantics.",
      "_why_team_shared": "The Entra rollout (Phases 3-10) depends on Microsoft Graph + MSAL.js correctness. A user-scoped plugin install drifts across machines and agent runs. Team-sharing via .mcp.json guarantees every contributor and CI run hits the same docs surface.",
      "_prerequisites": "None. Serves public Microsoft Learn content. No auth, no API key.",
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@microsoft/mcp-docs"]
    },

    "sequential-thinking": {
      "_purpose": "Structured multi-step reasoning. Tracks explicit thought chains for phase plans, architecture trade-offs, and cross-project audits — the kind of work the Entra rollout and Spacedrive integration produce continuously. Claude invokes it when a question benefits from visible step-tracking rather than inline deliberation.",
      "_why_team_shared": "Added 2026-04-21. Not plugin-managed — ships as a standalone MCP server via @modelcontextprotocol/server-sequential-thinking. Without this entry, a fresh session on a new dev machine lacks the tool unless the dev ran `claude mcp add` manually. Team-shared prevents that drift.",
      "_prerequisites": "None. Pure reasoning helper, no external services.",
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-sequential-thinking"]
    },

    "postgres": {
      "_purpose": "Direct query/schema tools for PostgreSQL. Phase 11.1 (PR #121, merged 2026-04-26) shipped the dual-backend foundation: SQLite remains the daemon default, Postgres opt-in via `[database] url = \"postgres://...\"` in config.toml. PR 11.2 lands the instance-tier per-store dispatch + `migrations/postgres/global/` (14 files dialect-translated); PR 11.3 lands per-agent stores + `agent_id` row-level tenancy; PR 11.4 lands the K8s CloudNativePG deployment.",
      "_why_team_shared": "Anyone working on PR 11.2/11.3/11.4 needs to inspect Postgres schemas (esp. comparing the auto-generated `migrations/postgres/` against the existing SQLite tree at `migrations/`), validate FromRow derives against actual Postgres column types, and verify `agent_id` tenancy filter behavior on real query plans. Per-user install drifts; team-shared keeps PR-review consistent across contributors and agent runs.",
      "_prerequisites": "Set DATABASE_URL to a local Postgres instance OR a testcontainers-spawned one. Quickest fixture for PR 11.2 work: `docker run -d -p 5432:5432 -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=dev postgres:16-alpine`, then `export DATABASE_URL=postgres://postgres:dev@localhost:5432/postgres`. The MCP server gracefully no-ops if DATABASE_URL is unset, so leaving this entry committed is safe even for contributors not actively working on Phase 11.",
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-postgres"],
      "env": {
        "DATABASE_URL": "${DATABASE_URL}"
      }
    },

    "_disabled_linear": {
      "_purpose": "Issue/sprint management via Linear.",
      "_enable_by": "Rename to `linear`, add LINEAR_API_KEY, and commit. Only if the team moves issue tracking off GitHub.",
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@linear/mcp"],
      "env": {
        "LINEAR_API_KEY": "${LINEAR_API_KEY}"
      }
    },

    "_disabled_sentry": {
      "_purpose": "Error triage via Sentry. Complements OTLP tracing (Alloy → Tempo) by surfacing application-layer exceptions without leaving the agent loop.",
      "_enable_by": "Rename to `sentry`, populate auth + org/project slugs, commit.",
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@sentry/mcp-server"],
      "env": {
        "SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN": "${SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN}",
        "SENTRY_ORG": "${SENTRY_ORG}",
        "SENTRY_PROJECT": "${SENTRY_PROJECT}"
      }
    }
  }
}
